{"title_page": "Hans Eduard Meier", "text_new": "'''Hans Eduard Meier''', born {{date| December 30th 1922}} in [[Horgen]] ([[Switzerland]]) deceased {{date|July 15th 2014}}<ref>[http://www.rsi.ch/news/vita-quotidiana/cultura-e-spettacoli/Morto-il-creatore-di-Syntax-1458496.html]{{cite web\n  | url=http://www.rsi.ch/news/vita-quotidiana/cultura-e-spettacoli/Morto-il-creatore-di-Syntax-1458496.html\n  | title=Morto il creatore di Syntax\n  | lang=it\n  | year=2014\n  | id=RSI014\n}}</ref><ref name=\"Linotype.com\"/>, is a Swiss type designer. Creator of neohumanist [[typeface]] [[Syntax (typeface)|Syntax]]  at  Stempel Foundry. Also Barbedor (1984), Letter (1992) and Lapidar (1995). \n\n== Awards ==\nLinotype Syntax won TDC\u00b2 2000 ([[Type Directors Club]] Type Design Competition 2000) award under the Text/display type systems category.<ref>[http://www.tdc.org/news/tdc2000.html TDC News:TDC2 2000] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120728064508/http://tdc.org/news/tdc2000.html |date=2012-07-28 }}</ref>\n\nBitstream Humanist 531 Cyrillic won awards at Kyrillitsa'99 under text category,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.itcfonts.com/Ulc/2541/_sidebar1.htm |title=U&lc Online Issue: 25.4.1: The Winners |access-date=2008-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213181608/http://www.itcfonts.com/Ulc/2541/_sidebar1.htm |archive-date=2012-02-13 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> and \"bukva:raz!\" type design contests.<ref>[http://www.tdc.org/news/2001bukvaresults.html bukva:raz! results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080918043557/http://www.tdc.org/news/2001bukvaresults.html |date=2008-09-18 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.paratype.com/pstore/fonts/Humanist-531.htm ParaType: Humanist 531 font]</ref>\n\n== Typefaces designed by Hans Eduard Meier ==\n* ''Syntax'' - conceived between 1955 and 1964, metal cast by Stempel AG between 1968 and 1972, digitalized by Adobe in 1984, also released as Bitstream Humanist 531.\n* ''Barbedor'' - 1984.\n* ''ITC Syndor'' - 1986, [[International Typeface Corporation]].\n* ''Letter (Syntax Letter)'' - 1992, Linotype.\n* ''Oberon'' - 1992.\n* ''SNB-Alphabet'' -1994, for the Swiss Bank.\n* ''Lapidar (Syntax Lapidar)'' - 1995, Linotype.\n* ''LTSyntax'' - 1997, Linotype.\n* ''Syntax Serif'' - 1999, Linotype.\n* ''ABC-Schulschrift'' - for Swiss school primers, 2001-2008.\n* ''Elysa'' - 2002, Elsner+Flake.\n* ''Gesta Antiqua'' - 2004, Elsner+Flake\n* ''Meier Kapitalis'' - 2012-2014, Elsner+Flake\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Linotype.com\">{{cite web\n  | url=http://blog.linotype.com/2014/07/hans-eduard-meier-%E2%80%A0-july-15-2014/\n  | title=Hans Eduard Meier, \u2020 July 15, 2014\n  | lang=en\n  | year=2014\n  | id=Linotype.com\n}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* {{cite web|title=Hans Eduard Meier|url=http://luc.devroye.org/fonts-26271.html|last=Devroye|first=Luc|website=Type Design Information|publication-date=}}\n* [[Max Caflisch]], ''Die Druckschriften [1955 bis 1995] von Hans Eduard Meier'', dans: TM-RSI N\u00b0 6/1996.\n* Dossier Hans Eduard Meier, TM-RSI, N\u00b0 3/2014, pp. 1-26, contributions by d'Erich Alb, Roger Chatelain, Sumner Stone, Katharine Wolff, Max Caflisch. ''Typografische Monatsbl\u00e4tter''.\n* {{cite web|title=Hans Eduard Meier, a life dedicated to letter design|url=https://www.typotheque.com/articles/hans_eduard_meier_a_life_dedicated_to_letter_design|last=Jubert|first=Roxane|website=Typotheque.com|year=2012|publication-date=}}\n", "text_old": "'''Hans Eduard Meier''', born {{date| December 30th 1922}} in [[Horgen]] ([[Suisse]]) deceased {{date|July 15th 2014}}<ref>[http://www.rsi.ch/news/vita-quotidiana/cultura-e-spettacoli/Morto-il-creatore-di-Syntax-1458496.html]{{cite web\n  | url=http://www.rsi.ch/news/vita-quotidiana/cultura-e-spettacoli/Morto-il-creatore-di-Syntax-1458496.html\n  | title=Morto il creatore di Syntax\n  | lang=it\n  | year=2014\n  | id=RSI014\n}}</ref><ref name=\"Linotype.com\"/>, is a Swiss type designer. Creator of neohumanist [[typeface]] [[Syntax (typeface)|Syntax]]  at  Stempel Foundry. Also Barbedor (1984), Letter (1992) and Lapidar (1995). \n\n== Awards ==\nLinotype Syntax won TDC\u00b2 2000 ([[Type Directors Club]] Type Design Competition 2000) award under the Text/display type systems category.<ref>[http://www.tdc.org/news/tdc2000.html TDC News:TDC2 2000] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120728064508/http://tdc.org/news/tdc2000.html |date=2012-07-28 }}</ref>\n\nBitstream Humanist 531 Cyrillic won awards at Kyrillitsa'99 under text category,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.itcfonts.com/Ulc/2541/_sidebar1.htm |title=U&lc Online Issue: 25.4.1: The Winners |access-date=2008-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213181608/http://www.itcfonts.com/Ulc/2541/_sidebar1.htm |archive-date=2012-02-13 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> and \"bukva:raz!\" type design contests.<ref>[http://www.tdc.org/news/2001bukvaresults.html bukva:raz! results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080918043557/http://www.tdc.org/news/2001bukvaresults.html |date=2008-09-18 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.paratype.com/pstore/fonts/Humanist-531.htm ParaType: Humanist 531 font]</ref>\n\n== Typefaces designed by Hans Eduard Meier ==\n* ''Syntax'' - conceived between 1955 and 1964, metal cast by Stempel AG between 1968 and 1972, digitalized by Adobe in 1984, also released as Bitstream Humanist 531.\n* ''Barbedor'' - 1984.\n* ''ITC Syndor'' - 1986, [[International Typeface Corporation]].\n* ''Letter (Syntax Letter)'' - 1992, Linotype.\n* ''Oberon'' - 1992.\n* ''SNB-Alphabet'' -1994, for the Swiss Bank.\n* ''Lapidar (Syntax Lapidar)'' - 1995, Linotype.\n* ''LTSyntax'' - 1997, Linotype.\n* ''Syntax Serif'' - 1999, Linotype.\n* ''ABC-Schulschrift'' - for Swiss school primers, 2001-2008.\n* ''Elysa'' - 2002, Elsner+Flake.\n* ''Gesta Antiqua'' - 2004, Elsner+Flake\n* ''Meier Kapitalis'' - 2012-2014, Elsner+Flake\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Linotype.com\">